OL,6,F"It is clear in this case there was an
OL,7,Finfatuation," Mr Sands said.
OL,9,FJudge Recorder Luke Blackburn said
OL,10,FCroft's conduct had left her
OL,11,Fvulnerable to blackmail and corruption
OL,12,Ffor which she had received training.
OL,14,F"You formed a relationship with a
OL,15,Fprisoner, you became infatuated with
OL,16,Fhim," he said. "So much so you sent
OL,17,Fhim pictures and had a pillow at your
OL,18,Fhome with a picture of him."
OL,20,FRecorder Blackburn insisted: "The
OL,21,Frisks of that are obvious to anyone."
